<Author>Ben_melb
<Content>Impeccable Experience Spending just 1 night in the Mansion exemplified what they call the famous Texan hospitality.The website looked good but we were still apprehensive. After coming from NYC, Boston  D.C. hotel fees, the $350 a night fee we were paying for the Mansion seemed too cheap. The confirmation email sent was not very professional looking and was delayed, the hotel is not actually at the address stated on the confirmation but on a side street. We drove up and down Turtle Creek  the streets around about 4 or 5 times before having to call the hotel for directions, there is no way you would find this by accident. However, as soon as we stepped out of the car all that changed. The decoration throughout the hotel is in grand mansion style, from the huge foyer to the rooms themselves to the restaurant  bar.The reception were polite, informative and friendly. The concierge himself brought our bags to the room and gave us a run down on all the facilities of Dallas - tailored to our interests. The room was gorgeous and spacious with a beautiful courtyard and a living area almost like a small suite. As soon as we arrived complimentary ice cold drinks and snacks were sent to our room.The concierge remembered our names and our interests and greeted us every time we went in and out of the hotel. He recommended a place to eat, organised a complimentary car to take us there and back and even the next morning remembered where we had eaten and asked us how it was.There was a great complimentary breakfast with big servings in a lovely balcony restaurant.There was also a lovely pool and spa area that was serviced with waiters offering drink service.The bathroom was large and sparkling with a real bath mat and a separate area for make-up etc. Housekeeping comes twice a day which means you never run out of towels and the ice bucket is always full. Bottles of water are left in the evening on the bedside table.I can't fault the Mansion except they really undersold themselves in the first instance. I think the experience was worth much more. You can't get that quality accommodation in Australia even for twice the price.The location is a great area, we ended up walking back from where we ate dinner (an outdoor mall supposed to appear like a Manhattan street - it doesn't) and that was a pleasant walk along the creek. In the other direction is an entertainment district of restaurants, bars and clubs on Cedar Springs St.Recommend this spot to anyone visiting Dallas, especially for a first time. There is no other choice. 
