<Author>dstivescpa
<Content>Great - Understated elegance in a dull city The reputation of this gem is justified, but it never ceases to amaze me how some people moan and groan about a top rated hotel when they find it not up to their expectations. Some of the other reviews on TripAdvisor really make the Mansion sound like an average hotel. I found it to be wonderful. When I arrived the first staff member I saw (a bellman) greeted me and looked at my baggage tag. He said my name, welcomed me, led me to the front desk and from then on, every staff member called me by name. As I was settling into my huge standard room, which was beautifully furnished, a snack was delvered by room service, compliments of the hotel. Dinner in the Restaurant was expensive, but wow, what a meal. The service was personal and excellent in every way. Some reviews said the restaurant was stuffy. It doesn't have a drive through, but if you want a quiet first rate dinner in a truly 5 star restaurant, don't miss this one. The tasting menu proved to be an excellent value and featured some wonderful food. It was also a pleasant event to be in a jackets required - ties optional setting. Those not wanting to dress for dining and think jeans and a tee shirt are appropriate can eat in the bar where the same menu is offerred along with a piano player.Another special feature was a Mercedes sedan that delivered me to my business meeting location without charge. The Mansion is not a Ritz Carlton, a Four Seasons or a resort. It is unique and needs to be enjoyed for what it is. Look at their website for some great package deals. Discounts for the Mansion are also available on some of the travel websites. I booked at 40% of the standard rate. If you go to Dallas, especially on business, stay at the Mansion. 
